data.title: His Majesty Sultan Qaboos receives more National Day greetings
data.meta_description: Muscat: His Majesty Sultan Qaboos bin Said has received more cables of greetings from leaders of friendly countries and senior international personalities...
data.text:
Muscat: His Majesty Sultan Qaboos bin Said has received more cables of greetings from leaders of friendly countries and senior international personalities on the occasion of the 46th Glorious National Day.

The well-wishers expressed their sincere greetings along with their best wishes of good health, happiness and a long life to His Majesty the Sultan, and the Omani people further progress and prosperity under the wise leadership of His Majesty.

His Majesty received greetings cables from Sultan Hassanal Bolkiahof Brunei Darussalam, President Kersti Kaljulaid of Estonia, President Giorgi Margvelashvili of Georgia, President Borut Pahor of Slovenia, President Tomislav Nikolic of Serbia, President Francois Hollande of the French Republic, President Tran Dai Quang of Vietnam, President Dalia Grybauskaite of Lithuania, President Marie Louise Coleiro Preca of Malta, President Htin Kyaw of Myanmar, Sheikh Nawaf Al Ahmed Al Jabir Al Sabah, Deputy Emir, Heir Apparent of Kuwait, Prince Khalifa bin Salman Al Khalifa, Prime Minister of Bahrain, Aleksandar Vucic, Prime Minister of Serbia, Nguyen Xuan Phuc, Prime Minister of Vietnam, Anerood Jugnauth, Prime Minister of Mauritius and Dr. Yousef bin Ahmed Al Othaimeen, Secretary General of the Organisation of Islamic Cooperation (OIC).
